title: Incline's Haas, Schrage take I-A tennis titles
text:
Incline's Haas, Schrage take I-A tennis titles Jim Krajewski , jkrajewski@rgj.com 8:12 p.m. PDT October 19, 2015 NIAA logo 
Three of the top four seeds won titles in the Division I-A tennis tournament Monday at the Reno Tennis Center â€“ Plumas Courts on Monday. 
In boys singles, top-seed Zach Haas of Incline beat Ethan Gotts of Truckee, 6-4, 7-5. 
Mason Wittels of North Tahoe beat Hawley Jarrett of South Tahoe in the third-place match, 4-6, 6-3, 6-0. 
In boys doubles, second-seeded Louis Marin and Mickey Sullivan of South Tahoe, beat Kevin Cross and Colin Deurlington of Truckee, 4-6, 6-2, 6-3. 
In girls singles, top-seeded Anne Schrage of Incline beat Allison Tong, also of Incline, 6-2, 6-7 (5) and 6-0. 
Hetva Patel of Sparks won the third-place match over Melanie Nuckolls of Fallon, 6-2, 6-1. 
In girls doubles, Izzy Martinez and Paige Thorn of Fallon beat Devyn Hogan and Laney Rohlf of Truckee, 7-6 (2), 6-2. 
Annie Guerra and Maya Willis of Truckee beat Kayla Bekiares and Haley Lindsay of Fallon, 1-6, 6-3 and 7-5 in the third-place match. Read or Share this story: http://on.rgj.com/1LHu7ow TOP VIDEOS
